
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a specified location. It retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node using [get-nodes] for specific arguments like [limit], [offset], [order], and [direction], and appends these nodes to the path specified by the [add] slot. The code effectively collects and organizes input parameters for further processing.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
